  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Logistics Crew",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Logistics Crew Member (Full-Time)</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Job Highlights</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Career development opportunities</li>\n  <li>Open, friendly, and dynamic work environment</li>\n  <li>Attractive salary commensurate with experience and skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are seeking a dedicated and responsible <strong>Logistics Crew Member</strong> with a <strong>Class 3 or Class 4 Driving License</strong> to join our team. This role plays a vital part in supporting families during their moments of grief, ensuring that all funeral logistics and arrangements are carried out smoothly and respectfully.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Transport flowers, backdrops (all religions), and other logistics required for wake setups</li>\n  <li>Assist in the setup and teardown of wake locations</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely delivery of logistic items to designated locations</li>\n  <li>Maintain tidiness and accurate stock records in the warehouse</li>\n  <li>Maintain cleanliness of company vehicles, equipment, and facilities</li>\n  <li>Adhere to and maintain quality control procedures</li>\n  <li>Project a positive and professional image at all times</li>\n  <li>Solve operational problems and make decisions effectively</li>\n  <li>Perform other operational duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess a valid Class 3 or 4 Driving License as driving of heavy vehicle is required</li>\n  <li>Due to job nature, working during weekends &amp; public holidays are required</li>\n  <li>Able to use basic computer functions</li>\n  <li>Capable of safely loading and unloading heavy or bulky inventory items while working in non–air-conditioned conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
